org.forgerock.openam.sts.soap.publish

Interface SoapSTSInstancePublisher

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Runnable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SoapSTSInstancePublisherImpl

    public interface SoapSTSInstancePublisher
extends Runnable
    This interface is essentially a marker interface which allows Guice to inject a specific Runnable into the SoapSTSLifecycleImpl. The implementation of this interface is responsible for consulting the OpenAM home server for published soap-sts instances (via consumption of the PublishServiceConsumer), and then exposing them as web-services (via consumption of the SoapSTSInstanceLifecycleManager).

      • Methods inherited from interface java.lang.Runnable
